  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "Here's an overview of the legal framework surrounding money laundering:\n\n1. International Legal Framework\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- Egmont Group of Financial Intelligence Units\n\n2. Key Legislation\n- Bank Secrecy Act (BSA)\n- Anti-Money Laundering Act (AMLA)\n- USA PATRIOT Act\n- International Money Laundering Abatement Act\n\n3. Regulatory Requirements\n- Customer Due Diligence (CDD)\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) procedures\n- Suspicious Activity Reporting (SAR)\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Record-keeping requirements\n\n4. Criminal Penalties\n- Monetary fines\n- Asset seizure\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Imprisonment\n- Corporate sanctions\n\n5. Key Enforcement Agencies\n- Financial Crimes Enforcement Network (FinCEN)\n- Internal Revenue Service (IRS)\n- Department of Justice\n- Securities and Exchange Commission\n\n6. Reporting Obligations\n- Financial institutions must report large cash transactions\n- Mandatory reporting of suspicious activities\n- Cross-border currency transfer disclosures\n\nThis framework aims to prevent, detect, and prosecute financial crimes.",
